{
  "stem": "19690.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And we could, at that time, use the gym in the public school for the afternoon.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "So that's when we had our gymnastics.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And that lasted a couple of years, and then that was cut off.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "But in the beginning, we would do that.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There were-- there was one boy in particular who lived in our neighborhood, whom I was a good friend with until I was about six and a half years old.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "At that point-- we were the same age-- he joined the Hitler Youth and, overnight, became my enemy.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He would never talk to me anymore.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And any time I walked past his house-- which was all the time, because he lived on the way to the bakery-- he would taunt me and throw things at me, even that early.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "This was in 1936 and 1937.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] on our way to school, all the children in our neighborhood would walk together so that we could protect each other from the taunting and the rock-throwing and whatever else that would go on, which was fairly constant.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "There would be days when nothing would happen.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Then other days, a whole batch of them would come at us.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And the-- the bad thing was that right down the street from where we lived was a public school that I should have gone to, and then directly across the back alley from where our synagogue was was another public school.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So they would gang up on us there.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And we would have to walk past the other one to go to school.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So there were two places where we had to pass where we would be recognized.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Oh, the Jews are coming, the Jews are coming.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So it was not an easy thing.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
